# Flutter MVVM Architecture Rules

This project follows MVVM architecture with Bloc/Cubit as the ViewModel layer. Always maintain these patterns and structure.

## Rule Files Reference

All detailed rules are organized in modular files within the `cursorrules/` directory. Reference the appropriate rule file based on your task:

### Core Rules
- **Project Structure**: [mdc:cursorrules/structurerules.mdc] - Directory organization, file placement, naming conventions
- **Theme & Styling**: [mdc:cursorrules/themerules.mdc] - Theme configuration, styling patterns, design system
- **Feature Development**: [mdc:cursorrules/featurerules.mdc] - Feature module patterns, view/viewmodel guidelines
- **Data Models**: [mdc:cursorrules/modelrules.mdc] - Model creation, JSON serialization, data layer patterns
- **State Management**: [mdc:cursorrules/staterules.mdc] - Bloc/Cubit patterns, state management best practices (to be added)
- **Navigation**: [mdc:cursorrules/navigationrules.mdc] - Routing, navigation patterns, route configuration (to be added)
- **API & Network**: [mdc:cursorrules/apirules.mdc] - API client setup, network layer, error handling
- **Dependency Injection**: [mdc:cursorrules/dirules.mdc] - GetIt setup, service registration patterns (to be added)

## Architecture Overview

- **Pattern**: MVVM (Model-View-ViewModel)
- **State Management**: Bloc/Cubit as ViewModel
- **Dependency Injection**: GetIt
- **Navigation**: GoRouter
- **Network**: Dio + Retrofit
- **Local Storage**: SharedPreferences
- **Localization**: Flutter Intl

## Quick Reference

### Project Structure
For complete structure details, see: [mdc:cursorrules/structurerules.mdc]

```
lib/
├── core/                    # Shared utilities and configurations
├── data/                    # Data layer (models, repositories, sources)
├── di/                      # Dependency injection
├── l10n/                    # Localization files
└── presentation/            # Presentation layer (UI)
    ├── app/                 # App-level configuration
    ├── common/              # Reusable UI components
    └── features/            # Feature-based modules
```

### Naming Conventions
For detailed naming rules, see: [mdc:cursorrules/structurerules.mdc]

- **Files**: `snake_case.dart`
- **Directories**: `snake_case`
- **Classes**: `PascalCase`
- **Constants**: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

### Feature Structure
For feature development guidelines, see: [mdc:cursorrules/featurerules.mdc]

Each feature must have:
- `view/` - UI components
- `viewmodel/` - State management (Cubit/Bloc)

